oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Copper status and immune response of weaned beef steers that grazed endophye-infected (Acremonium coenophinlum, Morgan Jones and Gams) tall fescue (Festuca arundinacea Schreb.) was evaluated in a 6 month, bi-location study(Ridge-Valley [R-V] and Southern Piedmont [SP] regions ofVirginia).
